# Hjerterum / Boly Design System

**Canonical docs:** `docs/hjerterum/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`, `docs/hjerterum/PRD.md` §15, `docs/hjerterum/UI_UX_GOVERNANCE.md`

## Universal Boly Standard (every page)

All routes — `/homeowner`, `/nav`, `/finn`, `/los`, `/ops`, landing — must match the Boly look and feel:
- **Dark default** (`--bg-app: #020617`), professional Northern scenery tone
- **Not acceptable:** flat white full-page screens, light-only new features, isolated consumer CSS skins
- `globals.css` tokens + global classes (`.button`, `.card`, `.input`)
- Design-system: Toast, ConfirmDialog, PageSkeleton, EmptyState, Modal, FieldInput
- **Never** `alert()` or `confirm()`

## Theme — dark + light everywhere

- Default: `data-theme="dark"`
- User can toggle **light mode on every page** (including Finn, Los, guests)
- All colours via `[data-theme='light']` overrides — **no** always-light-only CSS for new work
- `finn.css` / `los.css` light-only model is **retired** (migrate to globals)

## Languages — Norwegian, Sámi, English

| Code | Language |
|------|----------|
| `no` | Norwegian |
| `se` | **Sámi** (Sámegiella) — NOT Swedish |
| `en` | English |

- Language selector on every shell (like Boly `Header.tsx`)
- All new strings: keys in `no`, `se`, `en` in `lib/i18n/*`
- No hard-coded user-facing copy in TSX

## Module contexts (not separate visual skins)

Finn/Los/Ops differ in **layout**, not fundamental styling. Shared: tokens, theme toggle, language selector, lane colours, toast/confirm/skeleton.

## Tokens — no magic numbers

- CSS variables only for colours and spacing
- Lane calendars: `--lane-*` + `laneCalendarStyles.ts`

## Component selection order

1. `design-system/` → 2. `ops/components/` → 3. `features/*/components/` → 4. global CSS classes → 5. new (promote if reused twice)

## Before finishing UI work

- [ ] Dark **and** light tested
- [ ] 320px viewport OK
- [ ] `no` + `se` + `en` i18n keys for new copy
- [ ] No white-screen / light-only styling
- [ ] No alert/confirm; touch targets ≥44px
